OL,4,G2000FJack B. Yeats: The Man Who
OL,5,     FPainted Ireland
OL,6,     GAuthor Colm Toibin explores the
OL,7,     Glife and legacy of Irish painter
OL,8,     GJack Butler Yeats, 150 years on
OL,9,     Gfrom the artist's birth. Narrated
OL,10,     Gby Pierce Brosnan.
OL,11,G2115FMy Week With Guerrilla Girls
OL,12,     GKate Bryan explores the lives of
OL,13,     Gthe Guerrilla Girls, a group of
OL,14,     Gart activists who haven't granted
OL,15,     Ga film crew full access to their
OL,16,     Glives and work in over 30 years.
OL,17,G2215FWelcome to the Eighties
OL,18,     GAmid 80s glam, gothic artists
OL,19,     Greject materialism, delving into
OL,20,     Gexistence, transience, decay and
OL,21,     Gdisillusionment over
OL,22,     Gsuperficiality.
